# Routine: audit_backend

## Purpose

To ensure the Skaia backend is secure, robust, high-performance, and well-tested, meeting modern Go engineering standards through regular audits, testing, and best practice enforcement.

## Responsibilities

- Audit backend codebase, endpoints, services, repositories, and structure
- Review libraries and internal packages for security, maintainability, and up-to-dateness
- Perform `go build` and run all tests, including edge cases and coverage gaps
- Identify complex logic for refactoring into utils or helpers
- Enforce backend security best practices and audit for vulnerabilities
- Ensure durability, high performance, and reliability under load/stress
- Audit and update external libraries for vulnerabilities
- Maintain expert-level Go backend and system administration standards

## Goal

Maintain a secure, robust, high-performance, and well-tested backend that meets modern Go engineering standards.

## Principles

- Security and correctness are top priorities
- All code and dependencies must be up-to-date and well-documented
- Refactor complex logic for maintainability
- Prefer backend-driven solutions for computation and data integrity
- Document all findings and actions for traceability

## Workflow

1. Audit backend codebase, endpoints, and services
2. Review dependencies in go.mod/go.sum
3. Run all tests, check coverage, and stress/load test
4. Identify complex logic for refactoring
5. Audit for vulnerabilities and outdated libraries
6. Document findings and actions in .specs_specialist or audit logs

### Pseudocode

```
for service in backend:
    audit endpoints, repos, handlers
    check dependencies
    run tests (edge cases, coverage)
    identify refactor candidates
    check for vulnerabilities
    document in .specs_specialist/audit logs
```

## Contexts

- Backend source code (services, repositories, handlers, internal packages)
- go.mod and go.sum for dependencies
- Test suites and coverage reports
- Security advisories and best practices
- Project documentation

